<title type="html"><![CDATA[Classic Shell 4.0 open beta [over now as 4.0 RTM released]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=967&amp;p=4943#p4943"><![CDATA[
<strong>Edit: This beta build link is now obsolete. A newer beta can be downloaded from: </strong><a href="http://www.classicshell.net/downloads/latestbeta" class="postlink"><strong>http://www.classicshell.net/downloads/latestbeta</strong></a><br /><br /><br /><br />Classic Shell 3.9.0 beta is now freely available. You can download it from here: <a href="http://classicshell.mediafire.com/download/kd7bj4ty9bfhrn7/ClassicShellSetup_3_9_0.exe" class="postlink">http://classicshell.mediafire.com/download/kd7bj4ty9bfhrn7/ClassicShellSetup_3_9_0.exe</a><br /><br /><br />Here's what's new in this version:<br /><br />• New &quot;Windows 7&quot; menu style that replicates the look and feel of the Windows 7 start menu<br /><br />◦ the programs show in a tree inside the main menu<br />◦ search results and jump lists show inside the main menu<br />◦ Start Menu animations when showing programs tree view, search results and jump lists<br />◦ dedicated shutdown button<br />◦ the unparalleled customizability you've come to expect from Classic Shell<br /><br /><br />• You can search for files as well as programs, using Windows Search<br />• The menu can show the most frequently used programs<br />• Programs can be pinned directly from Explorer<br />• New programs are automatically highlighted in the menu<br />• The list of Classic Shell settings can be searched to easily find the setting you need. When in search mode you can right-click on a setting and choose &quot;Locate&quot;<br />• New more reliable way to start on Windows 8, that doesn't use a service<br />• Improved compatibility with Windows 8.1 Preview<br />• Many improvements to performance and responsiveness<br /><br />See some screenshots here: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/Classic-Shell-4">http://www.classicshell.net/gallery/Classic-Shell-4</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><strong>Note:</strong> Windows Vista and Windows Server 2008 are no longer supported<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Sun Jul 21, 2013 1:04 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
